<title>USA: RESEARCH ALERT - Informix.</title>
<headline>RESEARCH ALERT - Informix.</headline>
<text>
<p>-- Hambrecht &amp; Quist said its analyst Jim Pickrel cut estimates for Informix Corp following its first quarter earnings report on Thursday.</p>
<p>-- Pickrel cut his 1997 estimate to a loss of $1.05 a share on sales of $625.6 million from a loss of $0.49 a share on sales of $715 million. He also cut his 1998 estimate to nil per share on sales of $845 million from a profit $0.06 on sales of $1.07 billion.</p>
<p>-- Pickrel noted &quot;severe revenue weakness&quot; at the publisher of database software, and he said issues from a high backlog of 1996 sales may impact revenues going forward.</p>
</text>
